ranslations of 1869’s Manual of the Velocipede, 1868’s Note on Monsieur Michaux’s Velocipede, and the 1869 operetta Dagobert and his Velocipede. It also reprints scores of rare images from newspapers and advertisements, analyzing how these magnificent machines captured the era’s visual imagination. By looking at how it influenced French attitudes towards politics, national identity, technology, fashion, fitness, and gender roles, this book shows how the short-lived craze of velocipedomania had a big impact.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aTechnology & Engineering / General.2bisacsh  avelocipede, cycling history, cycling and literature, operetta, French Second Empire, cycling and poetry, cycling manuals, Nineteenth-century France, bicycle history, sports and recreation, sports history, biking, bicycles, cycling, cheap bicycle, history of bicycles, bicycle manufacturing, French bicycle culture, bicycle culture, biking culture, prohibition, gangsternew york18th amendmentprohibition, gangster, new York, 18th amendment, gangs, mobsters, Chicago, 1920s, mob.1 aWhidden, Seth, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978168448437940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781684484379423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781684484379/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_CL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CHCOMSGSEN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK